      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. It sounds like there's a lot of potential for \"hidden\" or unexpected costs if a breach actually happens. Are there any typical ways these clauses can be \"sneaky\" or designed to catch people off guard? Like, what should I be looking for to make sure I'm not getting screwed over by wording I don't see coming?",
